The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | International | Di lover denied job at Pak institute 
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       Di lover denied job at Pak institute 
                            
	Islamabad, July 24 (PTI): The late Princess Dianas Pakistani love interest, Hasnat Khan, is back in the news this time for being denied a job in a prestigious medical institute in Islamabad.        
	Khan, a heart surgeon, was looking for a job in the Pakistan Institute of Medical Sciences (PIMS) after his return from London.        
	Following media reports that he was denied a job at the institute, Pakistan Peoples Party leader and health minister Sherry Rehman ordered a probe into the matter, The News daily reported today.        
	Caretaker health minister Ejaz Rahim had tried to bend the rules to allow Hasnat entry into PIMS. However, the ministrys joint secretary declared the doctor ineligible.        
	Khan was reportedly keen to take over as project director of cardiac surgery at PIMS. He was slated to get a salary of Rs100,000 a month.        
	Health secretary Khushnood Lashari confirmed that Khan had applied for a job but he was not appointed.         
	Khan, 48, was a heart surgeon at Royal Brompton Hospital in London before he quit and returned to Pakistan.         
	Khan met Diana at Royal Brompton Hospital when she visited a friend recovering from heart surgery.                                                                                                                                                                                    
